<br>
I've run Win2K on systems as slow as Pentium 200's.  It crawls, but it works.<br>
<br>
WinXP I won't install on anything below a PII 450.  Also, Win2K will run with 64MB RAM, but WinXP won't install  below 128MB RAM.<br>
<br>
Requirements aren't even close to the same.  yes, the do run the same basic kernel, but with all the added stuff to WinXP, you need a faster machine.  At least allof those added features cache to disk when you're running other things. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
